div.p:
Other titles of our Book are: 
          The Apocalypse of Moses (Syncellus); 
          The Testament of Moses (the Catena of Nicephorus); 
          The Book of Adam's Daughters (perhaps applied only to a portion of 
          Jubilees); 
          The Life of Adam (perhaps an amplified excerpt of our Book).

div.verse:
For the earth will not be clean from the blood which hath been shed upon it; 
            Cf. vi. 2. for (only) through the blood of him that shed it 
            Cf. Num. xxxv. 33. will the earth be purified throughout all its generations.

[paragraph continues] And his portion extendeth along the great sea, and it extendeth in a straight line till it reacheth the west of the tongue which looketh towards the south; 
            i. e. (?) the promontory on which Mt. Sindi is situated. for this sea is named the tongue of the Egyptian  Sea. 
            I i. e. the Gulf  of Akaba; cf. Isa. xi. 15.

And he prayed before the Lord his God, and said: God of the spirits of all flesh, 
            Cf. Num. xvi. 22, xxvii. 16. who hast shown mercy unto me,  And hast saved me and my sons from the waters of the flood,  And hast not caused me to perish as Thou didst the sons of perdition; 
            Cf. 2 Thess. ii. 3. For Thy grace hath been great towards me,  And great hath been Thy mercy to my soul;  Let Thy grace be lift up upon my sons,  And let not wicked spirits rule over them  Lest they should destroy them from the earth. [paragraph continues]

And in the three and thirtieth jubilee, in the first year in the second week, Peleg took to himself a wife, whose name was Lômnâ the daughter of Sînâ’ar, and she bare him a son in the fourth year of this week, and he called his name Reu; 
            Cf. Gen. xi. 18. for he said: "Behold the children of men have become evil 
            There is a play on the name Reu in Hebrew here (re‘û . . . rā‘û). through the wicked purpose of building for themselves a city and a tower in the land of Shinar."

And on that day 
            i. e. the 15th of Sivan. we made a covenant with Abram, according as we had covenanted with Noah in this month; 
            Probably, according to our author, on the same day of the month. and Abram renewed the festival and ordinance for himself for ever.

This law is for all the generations for ever, and there is no circumcision of the days, 
            i. e.? of the days preceding the eighth day. and no omission of one day out of the eight days; 
            Only on the eighth day is the rite to be performed. for it is an eternal ordinance, ordained and written on the heavenly tables.
